Implement a compile-time safe HTTP request builder using the typestate pattern.

States:

NoUrl, HasUrl, Ready (phantom type parameters).
API:

rust
HttpRequest::new()           // -> Builder<NoUrl>
  .url("...")                // -> Builder<HasUrl>
  .header("...", "...")      // -> Builder<HasUrl>
  .send()                    // only available on Builder<Ready>
Constraints:

.send() only compiles when URL is set.

Use PhantomData<T> for zero-cost state tracking.

Each method consumes self and returns next state.
Show:

Compiler errors when trying to .send() without .url().

Zero runtime overhead (check assembly or use std::mem::size_of).

  